The paper discusses a security vulnerability in computer systems (specifically, the Rowhammer bug) and proposes new attack and exploitation techniques. This suggests that the paper belongs to the category of Computer Security and Cryptography (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper discusses system-level optimizations and side channels, which could potentially fall under the categories of Software Engineering (cs.SE) and Architecture (cs.AR), respectively. The paper also mentions the use of Intel SGX, which could fall under the category of Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper proposes a new technique called memory waylaying, which could potentially fall under the category of Programming Languages (cs.PL).
